ss=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sfg1665702550701.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfg1665702550701.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfg1665702550701.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sfg1665702550701\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Device Translation Table\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Device Translation Table is a Development Object that maps Uniface output to device-specific output formats for printers and character-based (CHUI) screens. It makes it possible for Uniface to support a wide variety of hardware platforms, including their output devices.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__section_w1619ab1b5b1_w1620ab1b5_w1621ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__section_w1622ab1b5b3_w1623ab1b5_w1624ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d280023e56\">\n                     \n Characteristics\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">dtb</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ijz1665702550775.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ijz1665702550775.html\" title=\"An Untyped Library is a Main Development Object that defines a collection of objects that may be of different types, and which can be reused or accessed by other objects during development or at runtime.\">Untyped Library</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ulo1665702550460.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html\" title=\"A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\">Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfg1665702550701__table_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DeviceTableName</var>@<var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var>.dvc</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__section_w1625ab1b5b5_w1626ab1b5_w1627ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d280023e231\">\n                     \n Specialization\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__p_d96305e1_d96306e1_d96307e1\">Device Translation Table specializes Development Object in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__li_d39035e1_d39036e1_d39037e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__p_d96308e1_d96309e1_d96310e1\">It has a Library as parent object.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__li_d39038e1_d39039e1_d39040e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__p_d96311e1_d96312e1_d96313e1\">It has no child development objects.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfg1665702550701__p_d96314e1_d96315e1_d96316e1\">For Windows platforms, device translation tables are used for enhanced printing but not for the GUI.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531949\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531949\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Device Translation Table Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Device Translation Table A Device Translation Table is a Development Object that maps Uniface output to device-specific output formats for printers and character-based (CHUI) screens. It makes it possible for Uniface to support a wide variety of hardware platforms, including their output devices. Characteristics Characteristics Object type code: dtb Main Development Object? No Part of: Untyped Library Contains: Property Generalization: Development Object Specializations: — Compilation Output: DeviceTableName @ LibraryName .dvc Specialization Device Translation Table specializes Development Object in the following ways: It has a Library as parent object. It has no child development objects. For Windows platforms, device translation tables are used for enhanced printing but not for the GUI. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}